have, I am going to focus primarily
on proteins, nucleic acids and

00:06:01.160 --> 00:06:06.830
lipids. I think this will get you
far enough along to enjoy subsequent

00:06:06.830 --> 00:06:12.490
chemistry. Let's get down to
business and start with proteins.

00:06:12.490 --> 00:06:18.160
Protein comes from the Greek word
proteos which means of

00:06:18.160 --> 00:06:25.280
first importance.
And these are macromolecules,

00:06:25.280 --> 00:06:33.850
polymers of a sort. And they are
formed by polymerization.

00:06:33.850 --> 00:06:42.420
And the mer groups that go into
this macromolecule are called amino

00:06:42.420 --> 00:06:56.906
acids, formed by polymerization
of amino acids.

00:06:31.000 --> 00:06:56.630
We better get a grip on what amino
acids are. As the name applies,

00:06:56.630 --> 00:07:02.270
they must be compounds that have an
acid group. In other words,

00:07:02.270 --> 00:07:07.900
capability of donating protons.
And amino means there must be some

00:07:07.900 --> 00:07:13.540
kind of an NH formation.
Let's draw the skeletal structure

00:07:13.540 --> 00:07:19.180
of a prototypical amino acid.
We start at the center with a

00:07:19.180 --> 00:07:25.110
carbon that is sp3 hybridized.
And one of the terminals contains an

00:07:25.110 --> 00:07:31.330
amino group which consists of this
formation bearing nitrogen.

00:07:31.330 --> 00:07:37.550
The acid is given above. This is
carboxylic acid.

00:07:37.550 --> 00:07:43.770
Carbon double bond to oxygen.
And then the OH. And this H is

00:07:43.770 --> 00:08:00.540
capable of detaching. There
is the amino acid.

00:07:30.000 --> 00:07:35.000
The third bond goes to oxygen.
Three of the four bonds are

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:40.000
uniquely specified in every amino
acid. Three of the four.

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:45.000
And now the fourth one, this is a
tetrahedron so I am trying to

00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:50.000
indicate that this bond is receding
into the back,

00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:55.000
is variable. And I am going to use
the carrier variable R.

00:07:55.000 --> 00:08:00.000
And this is the term for the
substituent.

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:26.660
And this is nature's choice.
In principle, anything that will

00:08:26.660 --> 00:08:33.330
covalently bond with a sigma bond
can be put here.

00:08:33.330 --> 00:08:39.990
This means that there are thousands
and thousands of compounds that

00:08:39.990 --> 00:08:46.660
qualify as amino acids,
but in proteins, only 20 found in

00:08:46.660 --> 00:08:52.720
proteins. That is a short list.
It is a rather compact library.

00:08:52.720 --> 00:08:58.180
Let's take a look at the types of
substituents. And for that you can

00:08:58.180 --> 00:09:03.630
look at the table here in your
reading. This is from the table.

00:09:03.630 --> 00:09:09.080
It actually spills over two pages.
I know that is very hard to read,

00:09:09.080 --> 00:09:14.540
but it is more iconic just to sort
of symbolize that maybe somebody has

00:09:14.540 --> 00:09:32.546
done the reading and they say I
recognize that table.

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:25.810
There are 20 different R groups,
20 different substituents. And they,

00:09:25.810 --> 00:09:31.630
themselves, fall into four
categories. The R groups can be

00:09:31.630 --> 00:09:37.450
broken down into four categories.
First one is nonpolar, the R group

00:09:37.450 --> 00:09:43.270
is nonpolar. Clearly,
under that circumstance,

00:09:43.270 --> 00:09:49.090
we would have something that is
hydrophobic. Nonpolar groups would

00:09:49.090 --> 00:09:55.250
be less inclined to bond to water.
We have the option of polar groups.

00:09:55.250 --> 00:10:01.750
Polar with hydrogen bonding
capability. And such groups are

00:10:01.750 --> 00:10:15.100
going to be hydrophilic.

00:09:50.000 --> 00:10:16.400
There is a third group that has a
net charge, so the R group is

00:10:16.400 --> 00:10:22.790
actually net positive.
And so that means these are going

00:10:22.790 --> 00:10:40.646
to be strongly hydrophilic.
They have a very high affinity for

00:10:09.000 --> 00:10:15.000
water. And it turns out they will
function as basic in aqueous

00:10:15.000 --> 00:10:21.000
solution. And then the last group
is a set of substituents that have a

00:10:21.000 --> 00:10:27.000
net negative charge.
And this, too, are strongly

00:10:27.000 --> 00:10:33.000
hydrophilic and will act acidic when
dissolved in water.

00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:57.300
Now our bodies can synthesize only
ten of the twenty amino acids.

00:10:57.300 --> 00:11:01.610
You will read in advertising that
certain foods contain some of the

00:11:01.610 --> 00:11:05.920
essential amino acids,
meaning they contain some of the ten

00:11:05.920 --> 00:11:10.230
amino acids that we are incapable of
processing. And failure to consume

00:11:10.230 --> 00:11:14.530
this in the diet,
over a long period of time,

00:11:14.530 --> 00:11:18.840
can have deleterious effects
prompting, in the extreme,

00:11:18.840 --> 00:11:37.746
your exiting the carbon cycle.
You do want to watch your diet.

00:11:04.000 --> 00:11:10.000
There is one other structural
feature that is important in the

00:11:10.000 --> 00:11:16.000
amino acids, and that I want to show
with reference to a specific amino

00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:22.000
acid. Let's choose alanine.
In alanine, the substituent group

00:11:22.000 --> 00:11:28.000
is methyl CH3.
I can draw alanine as follows using

00:11:28.000 --> 00:11:53.230
the skeletal structure to the left.
Here is the amino group which I am

00:11:53.230 --> 00:11:57.690
just going to truncate as H2N.
And, maybe later, I am even going

00:11:57.690 --> 00:12:02.150
to get so bold as to put NH2
recognizing that it is not the H

00:12:02.150 --> 00:12:06.610
that is bridging to the nitrogen.
But let's do it this way. The

00:12:06.610 --> 00:12:11.070
carboxylic acid will go up here,
will go here, and then we will just

00:12:11.070 --> 00:12:15.530
put the methyl group.
Now, I could just as easily have

00:12:15.530 --> 00:12:34.526
written it the following way.
I could have done this.

00:12:00.000 --> 00:12:24.140
I could have put the amino group to
the right and the hydrogen to the

00:12:24.140 --> 00:12:28.280
left. If you look at these two,
at first glance, you might say I

00:12:28.280 --> 00:12:32.420
just have to turn it and he has
basically written the same thing.

00:12:32.420 --> 00:12:36.560
But upon closer inspection you will
discover that it is impossible to

00:12:36.560 --> 00:12:40.710
convert the one on the right to the
one on the left.

00:12:40.710 --> 00:12:44.850
In fact, they are not
superimposable.

00:12:44.850 --> 00:13:04.633
What we are looking at here is
essentially a pair of gloves.

00:12:29.000 --> 00:12:53.830
This is considered the left hand and
this is the right hand.

00:12:53.830 --> 00:12:58.660
And you can close the gloves.
You can make them fit one against

00:12:58.660 --> 00:13:03.490
the other. They will mirror one
another across a mirror plane,

00:13:03.490 --> 00:13:08.330
but they are not superimposable.
As opposed to something like, say,

00:13:08.330 --> 00:13:13.160
propane. If I take propane, which
is also carbon sp3 hybridized,

00:13:13.160 --> 00:13:31.053
in contrast it has methyl above and
below.

00:12:58.000 --> 00:13:23.660
And that clearly is perfectly
symmetric and does not have such a

00:13:23.660 --> 00:13:29.330
glove-like feature.
Such molecules that have,

00:13:29.330 --> 00:13:34.990
we say, a handedness are called
chiral, from the Greek word for hand.

00:13:34.990 --> 00:13:40.660
Chirality is the property of having
handedness, non-superimposable.

00:13:40.660 --> 00:13:46.330
Another term for these is
stereoisomers.

00:13:46.330 --> 00:14:03.726
We can consider chiral molecules
stereoisomers.

00:13:32.000 --> 00:13:40.200
And the different hands,

00:13:40.200 --> 00:13:44.600
if you will, are called enantiomers.
And we don't refer to one

00:13:44.600 --> 00:13:49.000
stereoisomer or the other
stereoisomer. We refer to the

00:13:49.000 --> 00:14:13.400
enantiomer coming from the Greek
word for mirror.

00:14:13.400 --> 00:14:32.800
Enantios is the Greek word for
mirror. These are different

00:13:57.800 --> 00:14:22.200
mirror images.
The other thing about these is that

00:14:22.200 --> 00:14:26.600
they are optically active.
And what they will do is take

00:14:26.600 --> 00:14:46.333
polarized light and rotate it
through a degree of polarization.

00:14:11.000 --> 00:14:35.400
Just to give you another example of
the difference between something

00:14:35.400 --> 00:14:39.800
that is chiral and not.
You see the boxes at the top with

00:14:39.800 --> 00:14:59.266
no distinguishing features?
They can be twisted, turned and

00:14:24.200 --> 00:14:28.600
made to superimpose over one another.
By putting these little features in

00:14:28.600 --> 00:14:33.000
the bottom corner, we render
these boxes chiral.

00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:37.500
And no matter how you twist and turn
this box, you won't be able to

00:14:37.500 --> 00:14:42.000
superimpose it on top of the other
box. Here is a more complicated

00:14:42.000 --> 00:14:46.500
molecule that can come chemically
identical but has a right-handed

00:14:46.500 --> 00:14:51.000
version and a left-handed version.
Let's talk about optical activity.

00:14:51.000 --> 00:14:55.500
The only reason I refer to this is
that it gives the labels that are

00:14:55.500 --> 00:15:00.000
used in referring to one
versus the other.

00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:04.000
If you have a light source that just
gives light that is randomly

00:15:04.000 --> 00:15:08.000
polarized, that is to say it is not
polarized, and then you put it

00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:12.000
through a polarizing prism so that
the light is polarized in a certain

00:15:12.000 --> 00:15:16.000
direction. In other words,
the electric vector is only in one

00:15:16.000 --> 00:15:20.000
direction. Now the polarized light,
here it is indicating that it is

00:15:20.000 --> 00:15:24.000
polarized vertically.
This is the optically active

00:15:24.000 --> 00:15:28.000
substance which could include an
aqueous solution of alanine.

00:15:28.000 --> 00:15:52.920
And, if the aqueous solution of
alanine consists of only one

00:15:52.920 --> 00:15:57.840
enantiomer, then when the polarized
light passes through that solution,

00:15:57.840 --> 00:16:02.760
the plane of polarization will be
rotated a certain amount by

00:16:02.760 --> 00:16:07.680
interaction of the light with the
electrons in the orbitals in this

00:16:07.680 --> 00:16:12.610
particular molecule.
And what you see here is an angle

00:16:12.610 --> 00:16:17.530
of rotation alpha where alpha is
proportional to the concentration of

00:16:17.530 --> 00:16:36.226
the chiral species.
And also the path length through the

00:16:02.500 --> 00:16:07.500
solution. If we put in both
enantiomers, we expect no change.

00:16:07.500 --> 00:16:12.500
If we put in one enantiomer, we
will have one direction.

00:16:12.500 --> 00:16:17.500
And so it turns out that the
different enantiomers will cause

00:16:17.500 --> 00:16:22.500
different directions of rotation.
And this is how they are labeled.

00:16:22.500 --> 00:16:27.500
The one that I have shown here on
the right will cause a clockwise

00:16:27.500 --> 00:16:52.280
rotation of the light.
And so it is termed D as in

00:16:52.280 --> 00:16:56.850
dextrorotatory from the Latin word
for right. This is the

00:16:56.850 --> 00:17:01.420
dextrorotatory form.
And then the one here on the left

00:17:01.420 --> 00:17:05.990
will cause the light - And I am
going to write h nu here.

00:17:05.990 --> 00:17:10.560
It is the plane of polarization of
the light that is rotating.

00:17:10.560 --> 00:17:15.140
The plane of polarization, if it
went through a solution that

00:17:15.140 --> 00:17:19.710
consisted of only the enantiomer
depicted on the left,

00:17:19.710 --> 00:17:24.300
would move in the left direction.
And, even though the Latin word for

00:17:24.300 --> 00:17:28.920
left is sinister,
they didn't call it sinistrorotatory.

00:17:28.920 --> 00:17:33.530
They call it levorotatory.
I guess they had to go the Slavic

00:17:33.530 --> 00:17:38.150
languages to get a root word.
Levorotatory is this one. Some

00:17:38.150 --> 00:17:42.760
will call this the positive
enantiomer and the left one the

00:17:42.760 --> 00:17:47.380
negative enantiomer,
but in most of the reading that you

00:17:47.380 --> 00:18:05.493
will encounter it will
be the D and the L.

00:17:32.000 --> 00:17:41.500
It turns out that only the L form of
amino acids are found in proteins.

00:17:41.500 --> 00:17:51.000
Only L enantiomer of amino acids
are found in proteins.

00:17:51.000 --> 00:18:19.090
But synthesis could give rise to

00:18:19.090 --> 00:18:25.290
both. And certainly chemical
synthesis will give rise to both.

00:18:25.290 --> 00:18:31.490
I am not going to spend much time
on carbohydrates,

00:18:31.490 --> 00:18:37.690
but just for reference,
the carbohydrates are also chiral

00:18:37.690 --> 00:18:43.890
molecules. It turns out that in
sugars only D form is metabolized

00:18:43.890 --> 00:18:55.780
by our bodies.

00:18:33.000 --> 00:18:57.830
You may have heard of invert sugar
or baker's sugar.

00:18:57.830 --> 00:19:02.660
This is simply the L form of the
various sugars.

00:19:02.660 --> 00:19:07.490
And this passes unrecognized
through the body.

00:19:07.490 --> 00:19:12.330
Honey contains the L form of the
carbohydrate because it is processed

00:19:12.330 --> 00:19:17.160
by bees, and the bees have a
different biological apparatus.

00:19:17.160 --> 00:19:36.653
There is science fiction where
somebody is after some grand event.

00:19:02.000 --> 00:19:26.330
Finds themselves at a strange place.
It always has to be a desert island.

00:19:26.330 --> 00:19:30.660
And they end up eating fruit that
happens to be chock full of energy,

